 <text id="F0901T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Mcilheney reports on the health of his soldier friends and discusses family finances.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>
  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">

    <opener>
     <name type="recipient">Harriet McElheney</name>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1864-11-29">Tuesday November the 29<hi rend="super">th</hi>, 1864</date>
      <name type="place">Headquarters of the Army of the Potomac</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Dear Wife</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>It is with <orig reg="pleasure">pleser</orig> I set myself to <orig reg="answer">an
     ser</orig> your kind letter <orig reg="which">wich</orig> I <orig reg="received">reseved</orig>
     on last Saturday and <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> was glad to hear from you and I am <orig reg="well"
     >wel</orig> at present and hope <orig reg="these">theas</orig> lines will find you all <orig
      reg="well">wel</orig>. I <orig reg="would have">wod</orig>
     <orig reg="written">wrote</orig> sooner but we got marching orders. We <orig reg="are"
     >ar</orig> just there <orig reg="where">whar</orig> Joseph is <orig reg="buried">bered</orig>
     and <orig reg="Philip">philep</orig> and me is going down as soon as we <orig reg="can"
     >kin</orig> get away to fix up his grave. Tell Pap that D. Nole said that another man come and
     got his son that lay with Joseph and if he comes he <orig reg="can">kin</orig> get Joseph. I
     seen John Mason and he <orig reg="said">sade</orig> that James <unclear>Fegan</unclear><pb
      n="2"/> is just below <orig reg="where">whare</orig>
     <orig reg="we  
 are">wear</orig> and he is <orig reg="well">wel</orig>. I <orig
      reg="have  
 seen">sean</orig> Marshall Donley, <unclear>Wilem Henry</unclear> and a lot more
     of the boys and there is a lot of them that we <orig reg="haven't">havnt</orig>
     <orig reg="seen">sean</orig> yet. You <orig reg="said">sade</orig> you <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
     <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> but if we <unclear>owe him</unclear>
     <orig reg="anything">ennything</orig> I <orig reg="don't">dont</orig>
     <orig reg="want">wont</orig> you to <orig reg="pay">pa</orig> him for I think he has got
      <unclear>enough</unclear> you <orig reg="can">kin</orig> see little what he <orig reg="would"
      >wod</orig> take in cash for his farm and let me <orig reg="know">nowe</orig>. You <orig
      reg="said">sade</orig> that you sent a <orig reg="bottle">bootel</orig> of numbersies I <orig
      reg="thought">thot</orig> you <orig reg="didn't">dident</orig> think <orig reg="worthwhile"
      >worthwile</orig> to send me <orig reg="anything">enny thing</orig> for I <orig reg="wrote"
      >rote</orig>
     <orig reg="every">evry</orig>
     <orig reg="week">weke</orig> and I <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> think you did but if you think
     it is <orig reg="too">to</orig> much <orig reg="trouble">truble</orig> to <orig reg="write"
      >rite</orig>
     <orig reg="every">evry</orig>
     <orig reg="week">weke</orig> I <orig reg="don't">dont</orig>
     <orig reg="want">wont</orig> you to do it. You never as much as<pb n="3"/>
     <orig reg="asked">ask</orig> me <orig reg="whether">wether</orig> I <orig reg="needed">neded</orig>
     <orig reg="any">enny</orig> stamps. I have a few yet. I <orig reg="won't">wont</orig>
     <orig reg="write">rite</orig> til I get <orig reg="one">won</orig> from you. Nothing more at
     present but <orig reg="remain">remane</orig> your husband.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute/>
     <signed>Sylvester McElheney</signed>
     <seg type="postscript">
      <name type="recipient">Harriet McElheney</name>
     </seg>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
